## Verification after applying patches

```bash
# Sanity: file still parses as Markdown
grep -c '^### ' TODO.md  # count unchanged gates

# Sanity: no stray "frozen" claim at v0.3.0
grep -n 'plugin-api-v1-frozen' TODO.md
# Expected: exactly one match, inside the v0.3.4 freeze subsection

# Sanity: all four patch locations changed
grep -c 'within 2 seconds when LSP is warm' TODO.md     # expect 1
grep -c 'experimental baseline' TODO.md                  # expect 1
grep -c 'Intermediate target: full index of 50k LOC' TODO.md  # expect 1
grep -c 'Gate (warm scenario)' TODO.md                   # expect 1
```

If any of the four greps return zero, the corresponding patch was not
applied. If any return more than one, the `OLD` string was not unique and
something else in the file was also matched — review manually.

