## Not patched (and why)

The following items were considered and left alone:

- **WSL2 Ollama endpoint hint in v0.4.2** (`http://$(cat /etc/resolv.conf...)`)
  — this is technically correct for Windows-host Ollama + WSL2 client, and
  is the kind of LMIC-developer-useful detail the project should keep. The
  exact `awk` pipeline may fail on some configs, but the fix belongs in the
  doc implementation, not the TODO line.
- **v0.8.4 benchmark measurement on 4 GB RAM machine** — this is already
  well-specified. The announcement paragraph lead-line (`~2GB RAM floor`)
  will need to be rephrased to match the `<2GB editor RSS (target)`
  framing adopted in README and PRODUCT; that's a content edit when the
  announcement is drafted, not a TODO edit now.
- **v0.6.3 disclosure email** — marked as a decision to be made when the
  time comes. No change needed now.
- **Backlog items** — scope and priority are the author's call, not a
  correctness issue.

